$interpreted: Jihasaha: ...Princess, we've found the circus troupe.
Tindoiimu: Are Sophie and the others all right!? Are they hurt?
Jihasaha: ...They've gained a member, but they're all fine.
Tindoiimu: Gained a member?
Jihasaha: ...You appear to care a lot for them.
Tindoiimu: Of course I care, they've been so good to me—
Jihasaha: By looking after you in place of Tingko?
Tindoiimu: ......
Jihasaha: Is Tingko that easily replaceable to you?
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: ...Jihasaha, I'm very sorry about Tingko...
Jihasaha: The Queen is waiting.
Tindoiimu: ......
???: Where is Jihasaha!? Why hasn't he come to greet me!?
Insect Soldier: Calm down, Your Highness! We found the Princess in this Alliance stronghold. That must be what's keeping General Jihasaha so long...
???: ...You mean my sister is here?
Insect Soldier: Y-yes...
???: I knew it. I KNEW IT! You only care about her, and don't give a damn about me!
Jihasaha: —Your Highness!!
Jihasaha: Please stop. You are the only Queen I serve.
???: ...Jihasaha, I thought you'd abandoned me...
???: Waaah...
Jihasaha: Go now. Remember to have a medic look at that wound.
Insect Soldier: Yes, sir... Thank you, General...
Jihasaha: You promised me you wouldn't lose your temper and bring others to harm again.
???: I-I'm sorry, Jihasaha... You weren't there to protect me, and I was afraid, and...
???: ...I hate myself for doing it too... Wahh...
Jihasaha: ...It's my fault, allowing that to happen.
Jihasaha: We've cleared this stronghold of Alliance forces now. You've nothing to fear.
???: ...Really? There's not a single survivor left? You know, I'm not as strong as Tindoiimu...
Jihasaha: ...I'd never let you be in harm's way. Relax.
???: Okay, I believe you... You're the only person I can rely on in this world, don't you ever forget that~
Jihasaha: ......
???: Jihasaha, that person behind you...
Tindoiimu: Tachilaanda...
Tachilaanda: ...Sis? What are you wearing...
Jihasaha: The Alliance were out to kill the Princess, so she disguised herself as a man.
Tindoiimu: ...I trust you've been well.
Tachilaanda: ...Yeah! I'm doing well~ I'm so happy to see you again, Sis.
Tachilaanda: You've no idea... how much I missed you. I thought I'd never see you again, wah...
Tindoiimu: ......
Tachilaanda: Tindoiimu... aren't you happy to see me?
Tindoiimu: No, it's not that...
Tachilaanda: Is it because... I'm squatting in your rightful place on the throne?
Tachilaanda: I don't wanna either! I could never compare to you!
Tachilaanda: But everybody's dead, and you've devoted yourself to the Martial Arts Tourney, so if I didn't take the throne... Can you blame me...
Tindoiimu: I don't blame you. It's my fault for forcing it upon you. I'm sorry, Tachilaanda.
Tachilaanda: ......
Tachilaanda: ...I just want you to know, I only did it for you and the Insect Tribe.
Tachilaanda: I mean, it's been no end of trouble for me, but I'm just about managing~
Tachilaanda: Since you admit that I'm the Queen of the Insect Tribe, can I give you orders now?
Jihasaha: Your Majesty—
Tachilaanda: What, aren't I the boss of her now!?
Tachilaanda: I thought you said you'd serve me as your Queen, Jihasaha...
Tindoiimu: ...Yes, you're the Queen. What is your command?
Tachilaanda: ......
Tachilaanda: Sis~ Come train with me a while, okay?~
Tachilaanda: Jihasaha taught you a lot before, but now he's giving me lessons in combat, and I've gotten real good~
Tindoiimu: ...Yes, Your Majesty.
Tachilaanda: Awesome~
Tachilaanda: By the way, Sis~ You mustn't go easy just for my sake. But I forbid you from beating me, too~
Tindoiimu: What...
Tachilaanda: To go easy on me would be to disrespect the throne. To win against me would also be to disrespect the throne. Either way you'll lose your head~
Tachilaanda: But don't worry, Sis. I'm definitely gonna beat you~
Tachilaanda: What's wrong, Sis? Don't tell me that's all you've got. You're not allowed to lose on purpose~
Tachilaanda: You wouldn't dare look down upon the Queen, would you, Sis?
Tachilaanda: Ow, that hurts... Damn, am I gonna lose...? But a truly loyal subject wouldn't dare beat me...
Tindoiimu: (...Not allowed to hold back, and not allowed to win either... Is Tachilaanda looking for an excuse to kill me?)
Tachilaanda: You're—getting—distracted!
Tachilaanda: Here I come, Sis!
Tachilaanda: Why'd you stop me, Jihasaha?
Jihasaha: ...Enough.
Tachilaanda: ......
Tachilaanda: You worry too much, I was only playing with her.
Tachilaanda: She's my only sister. I couldn't bear to see her lose her head~
Jihasaha: ......
Tindoiimu: ......
Tachilaanda: You've always been close with Jihasaha, Sis. I'll let you both catch up for a bit~
Tachilaanda: But remember, Jihasaha is my servant now. You can't have him all to yourself anymore~
Tachilaanda: ...Your body's going as soft as your mind, Tindoiimu, it's really concerning.
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: (...What am I supposed to say to that...)
Jihasaha: ...I'll find somebody to protect you.
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha... Are you planning to stay with her?
Jihasaha: It's my duty to serve the Queen.
Tindoiimu: ...My sister has a talent for getting people riled up and sending them to their deaths, but she never gets her own hands dirty...
Tindoiimu: You know as well as I do how much you used to despise that about her.
Jihasaha: ...My lady... The princess is not as strong as you. She uses fear as a defence, but her fragility isn't her fault.
Tindoiimu: So even you've fallen for her excuses. She's not Tingko, Jihasaha!
Jihasaha: I know, Tingko is dead! You couldn't protect her!
Jihasaha: You're the one who's been riled up!
Jihasaha: You fell in love with someone you shouldn't have and missed your chance to destroy the Udumbara! And now, Tingko...
Jihasaha: The Insect Tribe have already been all but exterminated once before. I won't let it happen a second time.
Jihasaha: —If that means there's more blood and tears yet to be shed, then so be it!
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha!!
Jihasaha: You'll always be a princess of the Insect Tribe, and I'll always be willing to give my own life to protect yours.
Jihasaha: But this is the last time I'll ever bow to your authority. You're no longer fit to be our leader.
Tindoiimu: ...Jihasaha...
